@NODE INTRO "Introduction"
@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{FG SHINE}W - o - r - d - M - a - n - i - a 

@{FG TEXT}Version : @{FG HIGHLIGHT}1.0
@{FG TEXT}Release Date : @{FG HIGHLIGHT}9 September 1996.@{FG TEXT}
@{JLEFT}
@{BG FILL}                                                                            @{BG BACK}
@{BODY}

This program is designed to find anagrams of words and to performing pattern
matching functions on a dictionary of words.
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
Features include :-

	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Anagram searching.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Full pattern matching.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Fast dictionary searching.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Lots of criteria options.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}All lists can be saved.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Full user preferences.
	@{FG FILL}o @{FG HIGHLIGHT}ASCII dictionary support.@{FG TEXT}
	
@{BODY}
For  example,  giving  the program @{FG SHINE}"WordMania"@{FG TEXT} as the search string, it will
produce the following list of anagrams...
@{PAR}@{CODE}@{FG FILL}
	Adorn   Dam    Draw    Marina Now    Raw     Warm
	Aid     Dam    Drownn  Maw    Oar    Rid     Warn
	Aim     Darn   Id      Mid    On     Rim     Win
	Air     Dawn   In      Mind   Onward Rind    Wind
	Airma   Dimn   Inroad  Minor  Or     Road    Woad
	Am      Din    Inward  Moan   Ordain Roam    Woman
	Amain   Dina   Ionr    Morn   Own    Roan    Won
	Amid    Do     Iron    Mow    Radio  Rod     Word
	An      Doma   Main    Nadir  Radon  Row     Worm
	And     Don    Mad     Naiad  Raid   Wad     Worn  
	Aria    Dona   Maid    Nard   Rain   Wadi
	Arid    Dorm   Main    No     Ram    Wain
	Arm     Down   Man     Nod    Ran    Wan
	Aroma   Drai   Manian  Nomad  Rand   Wand
	Award   Dram   Manor   Nor    Random War    
	Awn     Dram   Mara    Norm   Rani   Ward


@{BODY}@{FG TEXT}
Or  giving  it the pattern @{FG SHINE}"*rian"@{FG TEXT} (meaning all words ending in @{FG SHINE}'rian'@{FG TEXT}) will
give this output...
@{PAR}@{CODE}@{FG FILL}
	Abecedarian         Latitudinarian      Stentorian
	Agrarian            Libertarian         Totalitarian
	Antiquarian         Librarian           Utilitarian
	Authoritarian       Nonagenarian        Valedictorian
	Barbarian           Octogenarian        Valetudinarian
	Centenarian         Parliamentarian     Vegetarian
	Disciplinarian      Pedestrian          Veterinarian
	Equestrian          Proletarian         Vulgarian     
	Historian           Riparian
	Humanitarian        Sectarian      
@{BODY}@{FG TEXT}


The  program  can  also be used to limit the search engine, by searching for
words within particular length limits, and by looking for words with certain
letters in.


WordMania  can  be  used  to  solve many word puzzles, such as the @{FG HIGHLIGHT}"SUNDIAL"@{FG TEXT}
puzzle  that occurs in @{FG HIGHLIGHT}"The Sun"@{FG TEXT} everyday.  WordMania can also act as an aid
to  solving  many other word puzzles, such as normal crosswords and clueless
crosswords,  and  if you run it on a fast amiga you could use it to cheat on
the  T.V.   program  @{FG HIGHLIGHT}"Countdown"@{FG TEXT}  (Although  how  you  go about getting your
computer  into  the  T.V.   studios  is something that isn't covered in this
document :)

@ENDNODE
